solution.p:
Solving for y in both equations we find that 
                           \begin{cases}y=x^2-24\\ y=x-12\end{cases}
                           Any pair of values (x,y) which is a solution must satisfy both of these equations. In particular, the y-coordinates of any solution have to both equal  x^2-24 and x-12.

hint.p:
The determinant of 
                           \pmatrix{a \amp b \\ c \amp d }
                           is ad-bc.

The determinant of 
                           \pmatrix{a \amp b \\ c \amp d }
                           is ad-bc.

